name: My Sharona
comments: Nr 1 US; entered the Hot 100 charts on June 23, 1979 and reached number one nine weeks later on August 25, 1979 where it remained for six weeks. Billboard named "My Sharona" the number one single of 1979. Today, it still ranks as one of the biggest selling singles of the rock era. Trivia: On Mar 24, 2020, the two surviving members of The Knack posted a sponanous clip on Youtube seeing them play to a backing track. With the singer having passed away, the only lyrics were "Bye Corona" at the end.
